<h2>Broken bone (single fracture) and Weakness</h2>
<p>WebMD Symptom Checker helps you find the most common medical conditions indicated by the symptoms broken bone (single fracture) and weakness including Broken (Colles fractured) wrist, Broken (Smith fracture) wrist, and Brachial plexus nerve injury.</p>
<p>There  are 4 conditions  associated with broken bone (single fracture) and weakness. The links below will provide you with more detailed information on these medical conditions from the WebMD Symptom Checker and help provide a better understanding of causes and treatment of these related conditions.</p>
</div>
